description:
The Copenhagen International Parents Meetup brings together mums and dads from all around the world who have made Copenhagen their home.

If you have just relocated here with your family or have lived in Copenhagen for some time and now have a little one on the way, the CIP Meetup can help you find friends and support.

We have a variety of events, including mums' nights out, newcomer welcomes, expecting and newborn get togethers, toddler playgroups and family days out.

We know that moving to a new country with young children can seem daunting, so join our relaxed and supportive network to make new friends for you and your little ones.

We look forward to meeting you!

description: Storytelling for children in English is a new group, which aspires to create a venue for interactive storytelling in Copenhagen for children from the age of 2.5 to 12. I am a professional actress and storyteller living in Copenhagen. Winning Storytelling competitions a couple of times here in Copenhagen has lead to invitations to tell stories around the world. Last time was in February in Edinbourgh 2013. I was invited by the Danish Cultural Institute and the Scottish Storytelling House to tell at a mini Scandinavian Storytelling Festival. 2011 brought me to St. Johns in New Foundland, Canada to talk and tell at the National Storytelling Conference of Canada. Here I was asked to talk about the way I use interactive storytelling tools when teaching kids in schools and kindergartens. See more in the book "Levende Fortælling" which I am the co- author of, Dansk Psykologisk Forlag, 2011. During the 30 years of my career I have entertained thousands of children with stories, plays and songs, games and creative workshops. I feel it is time to reach out to the English speaking audience in Copenhagen and start building a venue for them. I hope this has your interest and that you want to help build a community of sharing stories, ideas and needs, so that the future can bring all that we want to have... in the form of a fun storytelling platform.... beginning here.
name: Storytelling in english for children

description: Are your lucky friends not Dads and can still party all night and sleep all day? Have those wild social invites stopped rolling in? Or simply are your friends selfishly in another country altogether? Then Dads is for you!!! This is a group for Dads who do less fun stuff than they used to. The idea is to provide easy activities, at times when child burdens are at a minimum. These will include many events where children can come and some where the child has gone to bed. We will try to walk the fine line between enjoying what the city has to offer and not being uptight cultural snobs, combined with making it as easy as possible with the kiddie-winks. Events will be about once a month, unless one of you hardworking souls wants to pick up the reins. Non-Dads are welcome, but there will be a strict ban on talking about waking up late or partying all night (Dads need not know what they are missing). Even women are most welcome, but let’s limit the number of hot single girls. I am particularly uninteresting when speaking Danish, so I recommend English speaking to me, but I am happy for you guys to all speak Danish about me behind my back.
name: Dads who think they're cool!

description:
Jeg er Adoption Life Coach og har 45 års erfaring som adopteret fra Indien. Jeg kom selv til Danmark da jeg var 8 1/2 måned. Jeg har udgivet min først bog omkring det, at være adopteret, vokse op i et dansk samfund og dybere videnskab omkring Adoption og psykologien i det, at blive adopteret og hvordan det i nogen tilfælde kan påvirke vores liv som adopteret igennem vores opvækst.
Min bog er udgivet i USA på et amerikansk forlag og hedder One Voice Empowering Life Lessons About Adoption og kan købes som paperback og ebook på amazon. Jeg ved hvordan vi tænker og føler som adopteret og i de fleste tilfælde kan vi ikke sætte ord på hvad det er. Jeg vil gerne skabe opmærksomhed omkring Adoption i Danmark og USA. Jeg har dedikeret mit liv til Adoption idag og har min egen coaching virksomhed www.adoptionlifecoach.org.

Jeg coacher adopteret børn, teenagers, voksne adopteret og deres forældre for at hjælpe dem med at forstå sig selv og de tanker og følelser vi har og hvordan det påvirker vores liv. Igennem Meetup vil jeg gerne skabe et community for adopteret uanset hvor de er adopteret fra. Jeg ser frem til, at høre fra jer som adopteret og blive medlem af gruppen er så vi kan mødes og udveksle erfaringer. Glæder mig til, at se jer. Bedste hilsener Ranjanna Mariia Hvenegaard
Adoption Life Coach Mobil: +45 24 23 11 80

description:
Calling all parents and toddlers from the ages 3 to 5. Basically all those who are not in the kindergarten. Let's get together in our beautiful neighbourhood and create some great fun activities for our children.

We can have fun cooking together, playing together, learning together, dance together, or sign up for activities together for our children at convenient times and in our area - for example our building has a room that can be used. We can decide ourselves how to make this fun for both children and adults alike!

We can have plan and have brunch together every now and then or dinner or ... :-).

And most importantly let us get to know each other and create a network for our children locally. We will speak English, Danish, danglish, or whatever we feel like.

Moms and dads alike can join. Bring one, two, 10 children, or even sometimes come without the children :-).

Looking forward to really meeting you all!

description: Storytelling for children in English is a new group, which aspires to create a venue for interactive storytelling in Copenhagen for children from the age of 2.5 to 12. I am a professional actress and storyteller living in Copenhagen. Winning Storytelling competitions a couple of times here in Copenhagen has lead to invitations to tell stories around the world. Last time was in February in Edinbourgh 2013. I was invited by the Danish Cultural Institute and the Scottish Storytelling House to tell at a mini Scandinavian Storytelling Festival. 2011 brought me to St. Johns in New Foundland, Canada to talk and tell at the National Storytelling Conference of Canada. Here I was asked to talk about the way I use interactive storytelling tools when teaching kids in schools and kindergartens. See more in the book "Levende Fortælling" which I am the co- author of, Dansk Psykologisk Forlag, 2011. During the 30 years of my career I have entertained thousands of children with stories, plays and songs, games and creative workshops. I feel it is time to reach out to the English speaking audience in Copenhagen and start building a venue for them. I hope this has your interest and that you want to help build a community of sharing stories, ideas and needs, so that the future can bring all that we want to have... in the form of a fun storytelling platform.... beginning here.
name: Storytelling in english for children

description: Are your lucky friends not Dads and can still party all night and sleep all day? Have those wild social invites stopped rolling in? Or simply are your friends selfishly in another country altogether? Then Dads is for you!!! This is a group for Dads who do less fun stuff than they used to. The idea is to provide easy activities, at times when child burdens are at a minimum. These will include many events where children can come and some where the child has gone to bed. We will try to walk the fine line between enjoying what the city has to offer and not being uptight cultural snobs, combined with making it as easy as possible with the kiddie-winks. Events will be about once a month, unless one of you hardworking souls wants to pick up the reins. Non-Dads are welcome, but there will be a strict ban on talking about waking up late or partying all night (Dads need not know what they are missing). Even women are most welcome, but let’s limit the number of hot single girls. I am particularly uninteresting when speaking Danish, so I recommend English speaking to me, but I am happy for you guys to all speak Danish about me behind my back.
name: Dads who think they're cool!

description:
Jeg er Adoption Life Coach og har 45 års erfaring som adopteret fra Indien. Jeg kom selv til Danmark da jeg var 8 1/2 måned. Jeg har udgivet min først bog omkring det, at være adopteret, vokse op i et dansk samfund og dybere videnskab omkring Adoption og psykologien i det, at blive adopteret og hvordan det i nogen tilfælde kan påvirke vores liv som adopteret igennem vores opvækst.
Min bog er udgivet i USA på et amerikansk forlag og hedder One Voice Empowering Life Lessons About Adoption og kan købes som paperback og ebook på amazon. Jeg ved hvordan vi tænker og føler som adopteret og i de fleste tilfælde kan vi ikke sætte ord på hvad det er. Jeg vil gerne skabe opmærksomhed omkring Adoption i Danmark og USA. Jeg har dedikeret mit liv til Adoption idag og har min egen coaching virksomhed www.adoptionlifecoach.org.

Jeg coacher adopteret børn, teenagers, voksne adopteret og deres forældre for at hjælpe dem med at forstå sig selv og de tanker og følelser vi har og hvordan det påvirker vores liv. Igennem Meetup vil jeg gerne skabe et community for adopteret uanset hvor de er adopteret fra. Jeg ser frem til, at høre fra jer som adopteret og blive medlem af gruppen er så vi kan mødes og udveksle erfaringer. Glæder mig til, at se jer. Bedste hilsener Ranjanna Mariia Hvenegaard
Adoption Life Coach Mobil: +45 24 23 11 80
name: Copenhagen Adoption Life Coach Meetup
organizer.name: Ranjanna Mariia Hvenegaard

description:
Calling all parents and toddlers from the ages 3 to 5. Basically all those who are not in the kindergarten. Let's get together in our beautiful neighbourhood and create some great fun activities for our children.

We can have fun cooking together, playing together, learning together, dance together, or sign up for activities together for our children at convenient times and in our area - for example our building has a room that can be used. We can decide ourselves how to make this fun for both children and adults alike!

We can have plan and have brunch together every now and then or dinner or ... :-).

And most importantly let us get to know each other and create a network for our children locally. We will speak English, Danish, danglish, or whatever we feel like.

Moms and dads alike can join. Bring one, two, 10 children, or even sometimes come without the children :-).

Looking forward to really meeting you all!

category.name: parents/family
description:
The Copenhagen International Parents Meetup brings together mums and dads from all around the world who have made Copenhagen their home.

If you have just relocated here with your family or have lived in Copenhagen for some time and now have a little one on the way, the CIP Meetup can help you find friends and support.

We have a variety of events, including mums' nights out, newcomer welcomes, expecting and newborn get togethers, toddler playgroups and family days out.

We know that moving to a new country with young children can seem daunting, so join our relaxed and supportive network to make new friends for you and your little ones.

We look forward to meeting you!
name: Copenhagen International Parents Meetup
organizer.name: Marie-Danielle G.Hansen

description: Storytelling for children in English is a new group, which aspires to create a venue for interactive storytelling in Copenhagen for children from the age of 2.5 to 12. I am a professional actress and storyteller living in Copenhagen. Winning Storytelling competitions a couple of times here in Copenhagen has lead to invitations to tell stories around the world. Last time was in February in Edinbourgh 2013. I was invited by the Danish Cultural Institute and the Scottish Storytelling House to tell at a mini Scandinavian Storytelling Festival. 2011 brought me to St. Johns in New Foundland, Canada to talk and tell at the National Storytelling Conference of Canada. Here I was asked to talk about the way I use interactive storytelling tools when teaching kids in schools and kindergartens. See more in the book "Levende Fortælling" which I am the co- author of, Dansk Psykologisk Forlag, 2011. During the 30 years of my career I have entertained thousands of children with stories, plays and songs, games and creative workshops. I feel it is time to reach out to the English speaking audience in Copenhagen and start building a venue for them. I hope this has your interest and that you want to help build a community of sharing stories, ideas and needs, so that the future can bring all that we want to have... in the form of a fun storytelling platform.... beginning here.
name: Storytelling in english for children

description: Are your lucky friends not Dads and can still party all night and sleep all day? Have those wild social invites stopped rolling in? Or simply are your friends selfishly in another country altogether? Then Dads is for you!!! This is a group for Dads who do less fun stuff than they used to. The idea is to provide easy activities, at times when child burdens are at a minimum. These will include many events where children can come and some where the child has gone to bed. We will try to walk the fine line between enjoying what the city has to offer and not being uptight cultural snobs, combined with making it as easy as possible with the kiddie-winks. Events will be about once a month, unless one of you hardworking souls wants to pick up the reins. Non-Dads are welcome, but there will be a strict ban on talking about waking up late or partying all night (Dads need not know what they are missing). Even women are most welcome, but let’s limit the number of hot single girls. I am particularly uninteresting when speaking Danish, so I recommend English speaking to me, but I am happy for you guys to all speak Danish about me behind my back.
name: Dads who think they're cool!
organizer.name: Richard Baker

description:
Jeg er Adoption Life Coach og har 45 års erfaring som adopteret fra Indien. Jeg kom selv til Danmark da jeg var 8 1/2 måned. Jeg har udgivet min først bog omkring det, at være adopteret, vokse op i et dansk samfund og dybere videnskab omkring Adoption og psykologien i det, at blive adopteret og hvordan det i nogen tilfælde kan påvirke vores liv som adopteret igennem vores opvækst.
Min bog er udgivet i USA på et amerikansk forlag og hedder One Voice Empowering Life Lessons About Adoption og kan købes som paperback og ebook på amazon. Jeg ved hvordan vi tænker og føler som adopteret og i de fleste tilfælde kan vi ikke sætte ord på hvad det er. Jeg vil gerne skabe opmærksomhed omkring Adoption i Danmark og USA. Jeg har dedikeret mit liv til Adoption idag og har min egen coaching virksomhed www.adoptionlifecoach.org.

Jeg coacher adopteret børn, teenagers, voksne adopteret og deres forældre for at hjælpe dem med at forstå sig selv og de tanker og følelser vi har og hvordan det påvirker vores liv. Igennem Meetup vil jeg gerne skabe et community for adopteret uanset hvor de er adopteret fra. Jeg ser frem til, at høre fra jer som adopteret og blive medlem af gruppen er så vi kan mødes og udveksle erfaringer. Glæder mig til, at se jer. Bedste hilsener Ranjanna Mariia Hvenegaard
Adoption Life Coach Mobil: +45 24 23 11 80
name: Copenhagen Adoption Life Coach Meetup

description:
Calling all parents and toddlers from the ages 3 to 5. Basically all those who are not in the kindergarten. Let's get together in our beautiful neighbourhood and create some great fun activities for our children.

We can have fun cooking together, playing together, learning together, dance together, or sign up for activities together for our children at convenient times and in our area - for example our building has a room that can be used. We can decide ourselves how to make this fun for both children and adults alike!

We can have plan and have brunch together every now and then or dinner or ... :-).

And most importantly let us get to know each other and create a network for our children locally. We will speak English, Danish, danglish, or whatever we feel like.

Moms and dads alike can join. Bring one, two, 10 children, or even sometimes come without the children :-).

Looking forward to really meeting you all!
name: Teglholmen and Slusholmen Toddlers' Meetup

description: Storytelling for children in English is a new group, which aspires to create a venue for interactive storytelling in Copenhagen for children from the age of 2.5 to 12. I am a professional actress and storyteller living in Copenhagen. Winning Storytelling competitions a couple of times here in Copenhagen has lead to invitations to tell stories around the world. Last time was in February in Edinbourgh 2013. I was invited by the Danish Cultural Institute and the Scottish Storytelling House to tell at a mini Scandinavian Storytelling Festival. 2011 brought me to St. Johns in New Foundland, Canada to talk and tell at the National Storytelling Conference of Canada. Here I was asked to talk about the way I use interactive storytelling tools when teaching kids in schools and kindergartens. See more in the book "Levende Fortælling" which I am the co- author of, Dansk Psykologisk Forlag, 2011. During the 30 years of my career I have entertained thousands of children with stories, plays and songs, games and creative workshops. I feel it is time to reach out to the English speaking audience in Copenhagen and start building a venue for them. I hope this has your interest and that you want to help build a community of sharing stories, ideas and needs, so that the future can bring all that we want to have... in the form of a fun storytelling platform.... beginning here.
name: Storytelling in english for children

description: Are your lucky friends not Dads and can still party all night and sleep all day? Have those wild social invites stopped rolling in? Or simply are your friends selfishly in another country altogether? Then Dads is for you!!! This is a group for Dads who do less fun stuff than they used to. The idea is to provide easy activities, at times when child burdens are at a minimum. These will include many events where children can come and some where the child has gone to bed. We will try to walk the fine line between enjoying what the city has to offer and not being uptight cultural snobs, combined with making it as easy as possible with the kiddie-winks. Events will be about once a month, unless one of you hardworking souls wants to pick up the reins. Non-Dads are welcome, but there will be a strict ban on talking about waking up late or partying all night (Dads need not know what they are missing). Even women are most welcome, but let’s limit the number of hot single girls. I am particularly uninteresting when speaking Danish, so I recommend English speaking to me, but I am happy for you guys to all speak Danish about me behind my back.
name: Dads who think they're cool!
organizer.name: Richard Baker

category.name: parents/family
description:
Jeg er Adoption Life Coach og har 45 års erfaring som adopteret fra Indien. Jeg kom selv til Danmark da jeg var 8 1/2 måned. Jeg har udgivet min først bog omkring det, at være adopteret, vokse op i et dansk samfund og dybere videnskab omkring Adoption og psykologien i det, at blive adopteret og hvordan det i nogen tilfælde kan påvirke vores liv som adopteret igennem vores opvækst.
Min bog er udgivet i USA på et amerikansk forlag og hedder One Voice Empowering Life Lessons About Adoption og kan købes som paperback og ebook på amazon. Jeg ved hvordan vi tænker og føler som adopteret og i de fleste tilfælde kan vi ikke sætte ord på hvad det er. Jeg vil gerne skabe opmærksomhed omkring Adoption i Danmark og USA. Jeg har dedikeret mit liv til Adoption idag og har min egen coaching virksomhed www.adoptionlifecoach.org.

Jeg coacher adopteret børn, teenagers, voksne adopteret og deres forældre for at hjælpe dem med at forstå sig selv og de tanker og følelser vi har og hvordan det påvirker vores liv. Igennem Meetup vil jeg gerne skabe et community for adopteret uanset hvor de er adopteret fra. Jeg ser frem til, at høre fra jer som adopteret og blive medlem af gruppen er så vi kan mødes og udveksle erfaringer. Glæder mig til, at se jer. Bedste hilsener Ranjanna Mariia Hvenegaard
Adoption Life Coach Mobil: +45 24 23 11 80
name: Copenhagen Adoption Life Coach Meetup
organizer.name: Ranjanna Mariia Hvenegaard

category.name: parents/family
description:
Calling all parents and toddlers from the ages 3 to 5. Basically all those who are not in the kindergarten. Let's get together in our beautiful neighbourhood and create some great fun activities for our children.

We can have fun cooking together, playing together, learning together, dance together, or sign up for activities together for our children at convenient times and in our area - for example our building has a room that can be used. We can decide ourselves how to make this fun for both children and adults alike!

We can have plan and have brunch together every now and then or dinner or ... :-).

And most importantly let us get to know each other and create a network for our children locally. We will speak English, Danish, danglish, or whatever we feel like.

Moms and dads alike can join. Bring one, two, 10 children, or even sometimes come without the children :-).

Looking forward to really meeting you all!
name: Teglholmen and Slusholmen Toddlers' Meetup

Bonjour, Ce groupe s'adresse aux parents francophones qui sont en congé parental et souhaitent rencontrer d'autres parents pour partager des moments agréables en compagnie de leurs enfants.
J'ai pour idée d'organiser des cafés, des après-midi jeux, des balades-poussettes, des pique-niques...etc et tout ce qui pourrait venir égayer la routine des mamans et/ou papas avec leurs petits bouts!
J'ai hâte de vous rencontrer et espère vivement que ce groupe sera une réussite!
name: Parents et futurs parents francophones à Stockholm

category.name: parents/family
description:
We offer inspiration and fun for modern-day parents and care for their kids. 

We believe it takes a happy parent to raise a happy child. That is why we create a platform for parents to show their uniqueness and break away from family stereotypes. 

For parents: sport activities, mingles, networking, inspiration, and drop-in professional advice. 

For children: kids club with games and educational activities. 

For teenagers: a peer circle for chats and mingles.

description:
The Copenhagen International Parents Meetup brings together mums and dads from all around the world who have made Copenhagen their home.

If you have just relocated here with your family or have lived in Copenhagen for some time and now have a little one on the way, the CIP Meetup can help you find friends and support.

We have a variety of events, including mums' nights out, newcomer welcomes, expecting and newborn get togethers, toddler playgroups and family days out.

We know that moving to a new country with young children can seem daunting, so join our relaxed and supportive network to make new friends for you and your little ones.

We look forward to meeting you!

description: Storytelling for children in English is a new group, which aspires to create a venue for interactive storytelling in Copenhagen for children from the age of 2.5 to 12. I am a professional actress and storyteller living in Copenhagen. Winning Storytelling competitions a couple of times here in Copenhagen has lead to invitations to tell stories around the world. Last time was in February in Edinbourgh 2013. I was invited by the Danish Cultural Institute and the Scottish Storytelling House to tell at a mini Scandinavian Storytelling Festival. 2011 brought me to St. Johns in New Foundland, Canada to talk and tell at the National Storytelling Conference of Canada. Here I was asked to talk about the way I use interactive storytelling tools when teaching kids in schools and kindergartens. See more in the book "Levende Fortælling" which I am the co- author of, Dansk Psykologisk Forlag, 2011. During the 30 years of my career I have entertained thousands of children with stories, plays and songs, games and creative workshops. I feel it is time to reach out to the English speaking audience in Copenhagen and start building a venue for them. I hope this has your interest and that you want to help build a community of sharing stories, ideas and needs, so that the future can bring all that we want to have... in the form of a fun storytelling platform.... beginning here.
name: Storytelling in english for children

description: Are your lucky friends not Dads and can still party all night and sleep all day? Have those wild social invites stopped rolling in? Or simply are your friends selfishly in another country altogether? Then Dads is for you!!! This is a group for Dads who do less fun stuff than they used to. The idea is to provide easy activities, at times when child burdens are at a minimum. These will include many events where children can come and some where the child has gone to bed. We will try to walk the fine line between enjoying what the city has to offer and not being uptight cultural snobs, combined with making it as easy as possible with the kiddie-winks. Events will be about once a month, unless one of you hardworking souls wants to pick up the reins. Non-Dads are welcome, but there will be a strict ban on talking about waking up late or partying all night (Dads need not know what they are missing). Even women are most welcome, but let’s limit the number of hot single girls. I am particularly uninteresting when speaking Danish, so I recommend English speaking to me, but I am happy for you guys to all speak Danish about me behind my back.

description: Do you have a baby, but you'd like your life to be about more than just that? Are you self-employed and don't want your baby watching you working on the computer anymore? Are you on a waiting list for a vuggestueplads? We will set up a privately organised co-working-bring-your-baby-initiative! We have a big enough space and the motivation to help all the moms (and maybe even dads!) out there that want to get started again with doing what they love without their little one suffering from the circumstances (of the digital world/of the huge waiting lists for childcare from the kommune/of the weird fact that somehow society ended up in a way where everyone fights for himself). Let's get together, share ideas and set up a credible alternative!
name: Alternative Childcare (not only) for freelancers

category.name: parents/family
description:
Jeg er Adoption Life Coach og har 45 års erfaring som adopteret fra Indien. Jeg kom selv til Danmark da jeg var 8 1/2 måned. Jeg har udgivet min først bog omkring det, at være adopteret, vokse op i et dansk samfund og dybere videnskab omkring Adoption og psykologien i det, at blive adopteret og hvordan det i nogen tilfælde kan påvirke vores liv som adopteret igennem vores opvækst.
Min bog er udgivet i USA på et amerikansk forlag og hedder One Voice Empowering Life Lessons About Adoption og kan købes som paperback og ebook på amazon. Jeg ved hvordan vi tænker og føler som adopteret og i de fleste tilfælde kan vi ikke sætte ord på hvad det er. Jeg vil gerne skabe opmærksomhed omkring Adoption i Danmark og USA. Jeg har dedikeret mit liv til Adoption idag og har min egen coaching virksomhed www.adoptionlifecoach.org.

Jeg coacher adopteret børn, teenagers, voksne adopteret og deres forældre for at hjælpe dem med at forstå sig selv og de tanker og følelser vi har og hvordan det påvirker vores liv. Igennem Meetup vil jeg gerne skabe et community for adopteret uanset hvor de er adopteret fra. Jeg ser frem til, at høre fra jer som adopteret og blive medlem af gruppen er så vi kan mødes og udveksle erfaringer. Glæder mig til, at se jer. Bedste hilsener Ranjanna Mariia Hvenegaard
Adoption Life Coach Mobil: +45 24 23 11 80
name: Copenhagen Adoption Life Coach Meetup
organizer.name: Ranjanna Mariia Hvenegaard

category.name: parents/family
description:
Calling all parents and toddlers from the ages 3 to 5. Basically all those who are not in the kindergarten. Let's get together in our beautiful neighbourhood and create some great fun activities for our children.

We can have fun cooking together, playing together, learning together, dance together, or sign up for activities together for our children at convenient times and in our area - for example our building has a room that can be used. We can decide ourselves how to make this fun for both children and adults alike!

We can have plan and have brunch together every now and then or dinner or ... :-).

And most importantly let us get to know each other and create a network for our children locally. We will speak English, Danish, danglish, or whatever we feel like.

Moms and dads alike can join. Bring one, two, 10 children, or even sometimes come without the children :-).

Looking forward to really meeting you all!
name: Teglholmen and Slusholmen Toddlers' Meetup
organizer.name: Maame
